Use the standard library

This is how to remove_duplicates of numbers:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this numbers's length times:
      Remember that current is item i in numbers
      When current is not in result, then:
         Add result to current
      But, if not:
         Remember that j is 0
         Remember that new_result is []
         Do this result's length times:
            When item j in result is not current, then:
               Add new_result to item j in result
            End when
            Increase j
         End do
         Remember that result is new_result
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know

>>> remove_duplicates of [1, 2, 3, 2, 4]
[1, 3, 4]
>>> remove_duplicates of []
[]
>>> remove_duplicates of [1, 2, 3, 4]
[1, 2, 3, 4]